.SH "NAME"
blkdev_get \- open a block device
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ blkdev_get('u
.BI "int blkdev_get(struct\ block_device\ *\ " "bdev" ", fmode_t\ " "mode" ", void\ *\ " "holder" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIbdev\fR
.RS 4
block_device to open
.RE
.PP
\fImode\fR
.RS 4
FMODE_* mask
.RE
.PP
\fIholder\fR
.RS 4
exclusive holder identifier
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Open
\fIbdev\fR
with
\fImode\fR\&. If
\fImode\fR
includes
\fBFMODE_EXCL\fR,
\fIbdev\fR
is open with exclusive access\&. Specifying
\fBFMODE_EXCL\fR
with
\fBNULL\fR
\fIholder\fR
is invalid\&. Exclusive opens may nest for the same
\fIholder\fR\&.
.PP
On success, the reference count of
\fIbdev\fR
is unchanged\&. On failure,
\fIbdev\fR
is put\&.
.SH "CONTEXT"
.PP
Might sleep\&.
.SH "RETURN"
.PP
0 on success, \-errno on failure\&.
